The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 04 October is 430,843 (765.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 September, there were 48,765 new confirmed cases (86.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 32,813 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 49% (15952 extra cases).
